devdoc.author: Joshua Bijak
devdoc.details: Contract to deploy VCUSubtoken contracts for tracking.

params._VCUTokenName: Name of the ERC20 subtokenization, inherited from the parent VCU
params._VCUTokenSymbol: Symbol of the ERC20 subtokenization, inherited from the parent VCU
params._cap: Token minting cap to prevent overminting of the token.
params._creolSuper: Creol Super User address, currently in use during pilots and testing, will be removed on post-Beta release
params._vcuOwner: Address that owns the tokens generated in the subtokenization
params.decimals: Num decimals for token, default is 18

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * > Note: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
